

## 1. Problem Statement

Superwork currently has no in-platform mechanism for clients to pay for their subscription. Billing is managed manually (invoices, bank transfers, or external payment links), which creates:

- Delayed or missed payments
- Manual overhead for the Superwork team to track and reconcile payments
- No self-serve way for clients to manage, upgrade, or cancel their subscription
- Inconsistent billing cycles across clients
- Lack of automated dunning and payment failure handling

This prevents Superwork from scaling its client base efficiently and introduces revenue risk.

---

## 2. Goal

Integrate **Stripe** into the Superwork Client Portal to enable:

- Clients to subscribe to a Superwork plan on a recurring basis
- Support for **monthly, quarterly, bi-annual, and annual** billing cycles
- Secure card storage via Stripe's hosted UI components
- Automated invoicing, renewal, and payment failure handling
- A self-serve billing management experience within the client portal

---

## 3. Non-Goals

This feature will **not**:

- Support cryptocurrencies, ACH, or SEPA (for now — future consideration)
- Manage consultant payouts or internal compensation
- Replace Stripe's hosted invoicing for compliance purposes
- Handle VAT/tax logic beyond what Stripe Tax provides out of the box (future phase)

---

## 4. User Roles

### Client User
- View available subscription plans and billing intervals
- Enter and save a payment method (card)
- Subscribe to a plan
- View current plan, next billing date, and invoice history
- Update or remove their payment method
- Cancel or downgrade their subscription

### Admin (Internal — Superwork Team)
- View subscription status for all clients
- Manually apply discounts or coupons via Stripe Dashboard
- Override or cancel subscriptions
- Access Stripe Dashboard for full billing visibility

---

## 5. User Stories

### Client
- As a client, I want to subscribe to Superwork using my credit card so I can get access immediately without waiting for an invoice.
- As a client, I want to choose a billing interval (monthly, quarterly, bi-annual, or annual) so I can pick what fits my budget.
- As a client, I want my card to be charged automatically on renewal so I don't have to do anything each cycle.
- As a client, I want to view my invoices and payment history inside the portal.
- As a client, I want to update my card details if my card expires or changes.
- As a client, I want to cancel my subscription from within the portal without needing to contact support.

### Admin
- As an admin, I want to see which clients have active, past-due, or cancelled subscriptions so I can manage relationships proactively.
- As an admin, I want Stripe to handle retry logic so I'm not manually chasing failed payments.

